===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], Swedesburg had a population of 99, with 41 households and 33 families residing in the community.<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A76800&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref> The [[population density]] was 43.0 inhabitants per square mile (16.6/km<sup>2</sup>). The median age was 41.1 years. 18.2% of residents were under the age of 18, and 18.2% were 65 years of age or older. For every 100 females there were 67.8 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over there were 58.8 males age 18 and over.<ref name="Census2020DP"/><ref name="Census2020PL">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/pl?get=NAME,P1_001N,P1_003N,P1_004N,P1_005N,P1_006N,P1_007N,P1_008N,P1_009N,P2_001N,P2_002N,H1_001N,H1_002N&for=place%3A76800&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

Of the 41 households, 34.1% had children under the age of 18 living with them. Of all households, 58.5% were married-couple households, 7.3% were cohabiting couple households, 19.5% were households with a male householder and no spouse or partner present, and 14.6% were households with a female householder and no spouse or partner present. Non-family households made up 19.5% of all households; 19.5% of households were made up of individuals, and 7.3% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

There were 51 housing units at an average density of 22.1 per square mile (8.5/km<sup>2</sup>), of which 19.6% were vacant. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0.0% and the rental vacancy rate was 0.0%. All residents lived in rural areas.<ref name="Census2020DP"/><ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A76800&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

